nal law, cinema, and ideology, the contributions not only examine visual representations of international law, but they offer an essential insight into the functions fulfilled by these cinematic representations.Providing an extraordinary introduction to a variety of perspectives on core international legal questions, Cinematic perspectives on international law extends a valuable methodology by which international lawyers can critique the depiction of international law in film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational law. 0aLaw in motion pictures. 0aLaw on television. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh  aUnited Nations.  acinematic studies.  acriminal justice.  acritical approach.  ahuman rights.  ainternational law.  ainternational relations.  alaw of armed conflict.  apeace process.  atheory of international law.1 aBenatar, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapaux, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorten, Olivier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorten, Olivier, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDubuisson, Francois, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDubuisson, François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalkowska-Clarys, Martyna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFałkowska-Clarys, Martyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKang-Riou, Nicolas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoutroulis, Vaios, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLagerwall, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProst, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https:/